+# ADR 0001: Exceptions lake as a first-class learning organ
+
+## Status
+Accepted
+
+## Context
+The project already frames decision models as the operating system for agency, uses AIRCA as the decision spine, and expects a decision ledger to record inputs considered, options evaluated, owner, and final action. That creates a strong control plane, but it still needs a structured way to capture where reality resisted the model.
+
+Without that layer, overrides, low-confidence classifications, missing evidence, and governance conflicts remain buried in operational residue instead of becoming governed learning signals.
+
+## Decision
+Adopt an exceptions lake as a first-class learning organ.
+
+Every significant exception event must point back to a canonical address in the core architecture and must remain separable from the adaptation eventually promoted from it.
+
+The canonical address grammar is:
+
+`root.domain.capability.entity.instance.state.expectation.exception.adaptation`
+
+The lake records exceptions as structured events rather than free-text logs.
+
+## Consequences
+
+### Positive
+- preserves the difference between what was expected, what failed, and what changed
+- enables case, rule, taxonomy, ontology, and governance learning loops
+- creates a pressure map rather than a dead error log
+- lets AIRCA carry not only decision flow but also counterfactual memory
+
+### Trade-offs
+- requires stronger schema discipline
+- adds governance around disposition and promotion
+- creates more metadata work at capture time
+
+## Design law
+Ontology stores the world as currently believed.
+Taxonomy organizes the world for use.
+Exceptions lake stores where the world refused the model.
+Learning loop decides what gets promoted back into ontology, taxonomy, workflow, or governance.
+
+## Promotion rule
+No exception may directly overwrite the original expectation.
+
+Exceptions, resolutions, and promotions remain append-only and version-traceable.
+
+## Review trigger
+This ADR should be reviewed if the canonical address grammar changes or if the project collapses exception and adaptation into a single layer.
