+++ b/docs/architecture/habitat-alignment.md
@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@
+# Habitat alignment notes
+
+This pack was designed to fit a decision architecture that already assumes:
+
+- decision models as the operating system for agency
+- AIRCA as the governing spine
+- a decision ledger that records inputs, options, owner, and action
+- governance layering across worldview, institutional, operating, human, and technical layers
+- machine-readable appendix patterns for anchors, tags, and sidecars
+
+In that setting, the exceptions lake becomes the counterfactual memory of the system.
+
+## Functional role
+
+- core graph / ontology = what the system believes
+- exceptions lake / event layer = where reality resisted the model
+- decision record = how that pressure was governed
+- promotion log = how local exception handling becomes institutional learning
+
+## AIRCA bridge
+
+- `Architect` creates expectations and thresholds
+- `Inform` captures observations, evidence, and exceptions
+- `Rank` scores urgency and learning value
+- `Commit` approves resolution and promotion
+- `Act` updates rule, taxonomy, ontology, or governance state
+
+## Constraint
+
+Do not treat the exceptions lake as a junk drawer for generic logs.
+
+Every event must point back to the architecture and forward into a governed learning path.
